            "answer_text": "If the percentage of heavy Chlorine atoms is a then the percentage of lighter ones is 100-a. On average, in a hundred atoms there should be a heavy and 100-a light ones. And the mass of a hundred atoms is 100 lots of 35.5. The mass of the heavy atoms is a x 37. The mass of the light ones is [100-a] x 35. So, (a x 37) + ( [100-a] x 35 ) =35.5 x 100 37a + 3500 -35a = 3550 2a = 50 a = 25. In other words, 25% ",
